claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Table listing influenza vaccines by trade name, presentations, age indication, HA content per virus strain (µg/dose), route, and mercury content. Includes standard-dose egg-based IIV4 vaccines (15 µg/0.5 mL), high-dose IIV4 (60 µg/0.7 mL), adjuvanted IIV4 (15 µg/0.5 mL), and recombinant HA vaccine RIV4 (Flublok Quadrivalent: 45 µg/0.5 mL). Evidence: Flublok Quadrivalent is listed with 45 µg of HA per strain per 0.5 mL dose versus 15 µg/strain for standard-dose IIV4 vaccines The table shows Flublok contains 3× the HA antigen content of standard-dose vaccines but does not include any immunogenicity data; therefore it does not support the full claim about greater immunogenicity
